				<td colspan="2"><span>Excellent guide! It mirrors some of my own (so far still limited) experiences on hard adventures, especially the relative difficulty of the different themes. I consider myself still in the learning stage for hard Adventures and this helps quite a bit.
<br />

<br />
Small note: maybe it's worth mentioning doors (pet pieve of mine). IMO those make Takish (and some Mistmoore dungeons) more cumbersome than it already is. I invariably have doors closing on me when leaving a room with a pull, forcing me to stop and re-open them while the mob gets to swing at me. And targetting through doors sometimes just closes the door instead of targetting the mob /sigh. I really dislike the doors, and they can make a hard pull harder still.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
