				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Pulling Hard LDON<a name="26766"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 10 04 2:46 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>A few comments on the guide.
<br />

<br />
There are two types of shaman mobs in Ruj which can see invis. One is a goblin the other an orc that runs around buffing the other mobs. Thought I'd mention this so people don't think invis is completely safe.
<br />

<br />
The roamers in Ruj don't just saunter around, they run at sow speed. So don't let your group approach an intersection until you know you have cleared the roamer. Otherwise they can blind side you can take out a caster before you can react. Keep the mobs centered there. They can get stuck inside the side walls where you can no longer melee or nuke them. We left one in a wall at 4% and after the mission was over, we ran by and it came out at 35% and took out our cleric.
<br />

<br />
In rescues, the mob appears on track at the start. So if you have a ranger in your group you can go straight to him. I've actually gotten to the rescue mob before the emote was triggered, so we went after a named while waiting. I would only do hard rescues in Ruj, where the dungeon layout has many parallel paths, so large parts of it can be skipped on the way. Other themes can have very long linear layouts which may make the rescue or assassinate close to impossible.
<br />

<br />
You can get slaughters as low as 51.
<br />

<br />
I have a &quot;/target a&quot; hotkey which will target the closest mob starting with the letter a, which is anything but a named. When I approach a blind entry, hitting this key tells me if there is a mob right there waiting to ambush me. I usually pacify it, because even if it crit fails at least it didn't bonk me on the head and stun me with an aggro pull. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
