				<td colspan="2"><span>Good guide Steppy, except for the 'rujarkian being the easiest' comment.
<br />

<br />
If anything, (excluding Guk, as I have yet to a hard guk) I am 23-0 in Mistmoore and find them, even in weaker groups, even in a group that wiped twice in one aventure, we still manage to win.
<br />

<br />
On the other hand, I'm 19 or 20 and 4 in Rujarkian.  Collects have a tendency to be harder here, in my experience, and I've had one where our group kille 78 mobs on a collect 20 and failed, only to get the last item we needed 2 min later.  Ruj also tends to have hasted/sow'd mobs (like Takish) which means, if you don't land that preslow, the mobs literally tear you apart when you get to camp.  One other scary part about EC is (I think) the Halls Of War (or similar) where you begin the dungeon at a mean, mean intersection and have very little space to split.  This is the only pull in hard LDON where I still give lull a chance (and cross my fingies)
<br />

<br />
I find most parts of EF easy, but there are occasionally tricky areas (as there are in MM, but NOTHING compares to the intersections of EC).
<br />

